<TITLE>Scientific Programs at the NREL</TITLE>
<H1>Scientific Programs at the NREL</H1>
<HR>
<P>
Current research at the Natural Resource Ecology Laboratory focuses on seven themes:
the long-term response of ecosystems to global change, the functioning of agricultural
ecosystems, linkages between the atmosphere and terrestrial ecosystems, the interactions
of plants and animals, the role of humans in ecosystems, the synthesis and modeling
of knowledge gained from ecosystem studies and soil biodiversity.  Each of these
programs incorporates the
strength of an interdisciplinary approach to dealing with complex problems.  Programs
will continue to emerge at NREL as research shows the need for incorporating new 
disciplines and technologies and as synthesis of research results and scholarship
generates new perspectives on environmental problems.
<P>
<IMG SRC="http://www.nrel.colostate.edu/icons/sm_construct.gif">We are in the process of constructing home pages for every current project at NREL.  So the list here is not inclusive.  Check back later to see what's new!<IMG SRC="http://www.nrel.colostate.edu/icons/sm_construct.gif">
