<H1>Welcome to the Natural Resource Ecology Laboratory!</H1>
<HR>
<P>
The Natural Resource Ecology Laboratory (NREL) is an interdisciplinary
ecosystem science research center within the 
<A HREF="http://www.cnr.colostate.edu">College of Natural 
Resources</A> of <A HREF="http://www.colostate.edu/">Colorado State University 
</A>.
<P>
A chronology of recent changes and additions can be found in
<A HREF="NREL/whats_new.html">what's new</A>.
<HR>
<P>
For general information and access to NREL Project home pages, consult:
<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="NREL/nrel_info.html">About the NREL</A>, a comprehensive
  overview of scientific activities at the NREL taken from the NREL brochure.
  <LI><A HREF="NREL/programs.html">Scientific Programs</A>, access to
  information about current NREL projects.
  <LI><A HREF="NREL/people.html">People at NREL</A>: including clerical,
  laboratory and programming support services, and access to scientific
  staff curriculum vitae.
  <LI><A HREF="NREL/publications.html">Publications</A>: a complete
  listing of references to all NREL publications to-date.
  <LI><A HREF="NREL/facilities.html">Support Facilities & Staff</A>: computing
  and network resources, and laboratory facilities and field support.
</UL>
<HR>
<P>
For a summary of current activities at the NREL, please see:
<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="NEWSNOTES/current.html">Current Activities - The NREL News Notes</A>
  <LI><A HREF="NEWSNOTES/current.html#Seminars">Seminars at NREL</A>
  <LI><A HREF="NEWSNOTES/current.html#Positions">Open Positions</A>
</UL>
<HR>

