<tITLE>Agroecosystems</TITLE>
<center><H1>Agroecosystems</H1></center>
<HR>
<P>
Human beings practice agriculture, the cultivation of the soil to produce food and fiber,
over a significant portion of the land area of the earth.  Agriculture thus affects
natural processes at every spatial scale, from local to global.  In the late 1970's
Vernon Cole and his coworkers at the Natural Resource Ecology Laboratory (NREL)
developed one of the first programs for studying agriculture ecosystems (agroecosystems)
to be funded by the National Science Foundation.  Since then, NREL scientists have
focused on gaining a fundamental understanding of the biogeochemical flows related to the 
dynamics of soil organic matter (SOM) and the cycling of carbon, nitrogen, sulfur
and phosphorus.  Studies of SOM in agroecosystems and simulation analyses with the
NREL's Century model have provided a broad base of knowledge that is applicable to the 
dynamics of nutrients within ecosystems in general.  We are using this understanding
to address ecosystem questions at multiple scales of resolution in time and space.
Click <A HREF="../../ABOUTNREL/agroecosystems.html">here</A> for a more detailed description of
the Agroecosystems Research at NREL.
<P>
<H2>Agroecosystems Projects at NREL:</H2>
<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="ADAPT-I.html">ADAPT-I</A> - Regional Projections of C Dynamics with Global Change in the Central U.S.  
  <LI><A HREF="ADAPT.html">ADAPT-II</A> - Spatially Explicit Projections of C Dynamics with Global Change in the Central U.S.
  <LI><A HREF="AGROECOZ.html">AGROECOZONES</A> - Determination of Agroecozones for use in Policy Analysis 
  <LI><A HREF="PIAP.html">PIAP</A> - Within-plant distribution, varietal response and early season management of alfalfa foliar nematodes
  <LI><A HREF="PIAP2.html">PIAP2</A> - Characterizing the biologic and economic components necessary for the integrated management of alfalfa stem nematode
  <LI><A HREF="CLUC.html">CLUC</A> - A Hierarchical Approach to Integrated Assessment of Climate and Land Use Changes with an Application to the Central US
  <LI><A HREF="CROPS.html">CROPS</A> - Analysis of Production, N Dynamics and Profitability in Complex Cropping Systems 
  <LI><A HREF="CRP.html">CRP</A> - Assessment of the Contribution of CRP Lands to C Sequestration and CO2 Mitigation
  <LI><A HREF="EPA-E.html">EPA-E</A> - Agroecosystem Carbon Pools and Dynamics 
  <LI><A HREF="FUNGI.html">FUNGI</A> - Fungal Contributions to Soil Organic Matter Formation
  <LI><A HREF="NIH.html">NIH</A> - Population and Environment in the US Great Plains
  <LI><A HREF="KBS.html">KBS-LTER</A> - Process-level Interactions in Agricultural Ecosystems
  <LI><A HREF="KTSOM.html">KTSOM</A> - Environmental and Management controls on Soil Structure and Organic Matter Dynamics
  <LI><A HREF="LUCCI.html">LUCCI</A> - Land Use and Climate Change Impacts on Carbon Fluxes
  <LI><A HREF="SGS.html">SGS-LTER</A> - Shortgrass Steppe Long Term Ecological Research Project
</UL>
