<TITLE>Land/Atmosphere Interactions</TITLE>
<center><H1>Land/Atmosphere Interactions</H1></center>
<HR>
<P>
Improvements in our understanding of ecological processes have played a major
role in the unraveling of important problems in the atmospheric sciences and
geophysics over the last decade. Earth scientists have observed increases in the
atmospheric concentrations of a number of biogenic trace gases during this period;
their observations have had, in turn, a massive impact on the practice of ecology.
Scientists at the Natural Resource Ecology Laboratory (NREL), in collaboration
with colleagues at other laboratories, have become progressively more involved in
studying the interactions between ecosystems and the atmosphere as understanding
the effects of climate change has become a national and international priority.  
Click <A HREF="../../ABOUTNREL/atmosphere.html">here</A> for a more detailed description of
ecology and atmospheric science at NREL.
<P>
<H2>Land/Atmosphere Projects at NREL:</H2>
<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="../AGRICULTURE/ADAPT-I.html">ADAPT-I</A> - Regional Projections of C Dynamics with Global Change in the Central U.S.
  <LI><A HREF="../AGRICULTURE/ADAPT.html">ADAPT-II</A> - Spatially Explicit Projections of C Dynamics with Global Change in the Central U.S.
  <LI><A HREF="BOREAS.html">BOREAS</A> - Field micrometeorological measurements, process-level studies, and modeling of methane and carbon dioxide fluxes in a boreal wetland ecosystem 
  <LI><A HREF="CO2.html">CO2</A> - Response of a temperate grassland to climate change: Importance of biotic interactions and feedbacks 
  <LI><A HREF="../AGRICULTURE/CRP.html">CRP</A> - Assessment of the Contribution of CRP Lands to C Sequestration and CO2 Mitigation
  <LI><A HREF="EARM.html">EARM</A> - Grassland-Atmosphere Interactions: Analyses Using Coupled Ecophysiological, Ecosystem, Micrometeorology, and Mesoscale Atmospheric Models.
  <LI><A HREF="../AGRICULTURE/EPA-E.html">EPA-E</A> - Agroecosystem Carbon Pools and Dynamics
  <LI><A HREF="EOS.html">EOS</A> - Using Multi-Sensor Data to Model Factors Limiting Carbon Balance in Global Arid and Semiarid Lands. 
  <LI><A HREF="NADP.html">NADP</A> - National Atmospheric Deposition Program and National Trends Network
  <LI><A HREF="PLAT.html">PLAT</A> - Dynamic Land Surface/Atmospheric Parameterization
  at Different Spatial Scales for the South Platte River Drainage Responses of Hydrologic Processes to Potential Climate Change on
  Watershed, Sub-basin, and Basin Scales 
  <LI><A HREF="PCVC.html">Projecting Climate and Vegetation Change for the Central Grasslands Region.  National Biological Service Global Change Program.</A> 
  <LI><A HREF="REGION.html">Regional scale long-term ecological research and monitoring in the Colorado Front Range: Effects of Increased Nitrogen Deposition on Subalpine Forest Growth</A> 
  <LI><A HREF="MYCOT.html">Response of mycotrophic C3 and C4 rangeland grasses to atmospheric CO2 and water</A> 
