<TITLE>Long-Term Studies</TITLE>
<center><H1>Long-Term Studies</H1></center>
<HR>
<P>
Natural systems have rhythms and progressions over time that strongly influence, if
not dictate, the characteristics of individual components.  Variation in climate,
periodic disturbances and internal community dynamics are all involved in shaping
ecosystems.  Long-term observations are required in order to formulate meaningful,
testable hypotheses that describe and predict ecosystem responses to changing conditions.
Click <A HREF="../../ABOUTNREL/long-term.html">here</A> for a more detailed description of
the Long-Term Research at NREL.
<P>
<H2>Long-Term Research Projects at NREL:</H2>
<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="DART2.html">DART2</A> - Antarctic Dry Valley Nematode Communities: Establishment, Function and Response to Disturbances.
  <LI><A HREF="../AGRICULTURE/EPA-E.html">EPA-E</A> - Agroecosystem Carbon Pools and Dynamics
  <LI><A HREF="GCES.html">Global Change/Ecosystems Studies in the Colorado Rockies Biogeographical Area</A>
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.Colorado.Edu/INSTAAR/TEAML/ITEX/index.html">ITEX</A> - International Tundra Experiment
  <LI><A HREF="../BIODIVERSITY/SOILBIODIVERSITY/KBS/KBS.html">KBS-LTER</A> - Kellogg Biological Station, Michigan State University
  <LI><A HREF="LUQ/LUQ.html">LUQ-LTER</A> - Luquillo, Puerto Rico
  <LI><A HREF="LVWS/LVWS.html">LVWS</A> - The Loch Vale Watershed Long-Term Research and Monitoring Program, Rocky Mountain National Park, Colorado
  <LI><A HREF="MCM/MCM.html">MCM-LTER</A> - McMurdo Dry Valleys, Antarctica 
  <LI><A HREF="http://nadp.nrel.colostate.edu/NADP">NADP</A> - The National Atmospheric Deposition Program, Fort Collins Colorado
  <LI><A HREF="REFUGE.html">Role of edaphic factors and species life history characteristics  in dynamics of grassland and shrubland ecotones at the Sevilleta National Wildlife Refuge-LTER site</A>
