<html>
<head>
<title>ADAPT II</title>
</head>
<body>
<h3>Project Name: Spatially Explicit Projections of C Dynamics with Global
Change in the Central U.S. (ADAPT II)</h3>
Funding Agency: DOE-NIGEC <p>

Starting/Ending  Date: 1996-1998<p>

Description: <p>

This project focuses on making regional projections of global change impacts on C storage and
agroecosystem productivity.  Driving variable input for the model is derived from spatially explicit
data representing the region, which is organized with a geographic information system.
Regionalized output from global circulation models will be used to modify climate when driving
variables are altered to simulate future climate. We will provide information on crop yields to
researchers at Montana State University, and they will reciprocally provide information to us
about the probability of the economic and environmental "success" of particular management
systems as feedback into our ecosystem model. Model output from the linked
ecosystem/economic models will then be projected back onto the region to obtain spatially explicit
regional information.<p>

Significant Products to Date:  None<p>

Research Scientists and Collaborators:<p>

	NREL PI - E.T. Elliott<p>

	NREL Co-PI - K. Paustian, C.V. Cole<p>

	External Co-PI affiliation under the following categories:<p>

		CSU- G.A. Peterson, Dept. Soil and Crop Sciences<p>

		National- J. Antle (Mont. State Univ.), PI of separate but collaborative proposal<p>

