<html>
<head>
<title>AGROECOZONES</title>
</head>
<body>
<h3>Project Name: Determination of Agroecozones for use in Policy
Analysis (AGROECOZONES)</h3>
Funding Agency: USDA-ARS<p>

Starting/Ending Date: December 1995- March 1996<p>

Description:<p>

The purpose of this work is to define the spatial extent of agroecozones for the 48 conterminous
states.  We are responding expeditiously to provide information to policy and decision makers to
assist them with decisions being currently made. We are providing an analysis and evaluation of
one of the most widely applied and accessible databases, the Land Resource Regions (LRRs), and
subunits of the LRRs, the Major Land Resource Areas (MLRAs) which is spatially organized
information on land as a resource for farming ranching, forestry, engineering, recreation and other
uses. <p>

Significant Products to Date:<p>

Cluster analyses have been completed using the primary 181 MLRAs.  Those which concurrently
use normalized values of precipitation, growing degree days and available soil water holding
capacity are showing the most promise and we have completed clusters of 10, 20, 30 and 40
subunits (MLRAs).  The 1992 county level crop statistics are now organized in a coherent
database and are ready to include in the next phase of the analysis.<p>

Research Scientists and Collaborators:<p>

	NREL PI - Paustian/Elliott	<p>

	External Co-PI affiliation under the following categories:<p>

		Government Agency- R.F. Follet (USDA-ARS)<p>

