<html>
<head>
<title>GED</title>
</head>
<body>
<h3>Project Name:  Analysis of Past and Current Changes in Grassland
Ecosystem Dynamics in Asia and North America</h3>
Funding Agency:  NSF<p>

Starting Date:  10/1/96<p>

Ending Date:  3/31/99<p>

Amount Funded:  $199,959 for total project<p>

Description:<p>

Analyze the impact of changes in climate, land use, and vegetation of the Asian and North
American grasslands.  Analysis of grasslands will integrate isotope analysis, remote sensing, and
modeling techniques to assess changes over the past several decades and centuries.   <p>

Significant Products:<p>

The analysis will provide a spatial and temporal scale of change in grassland biogeochemistry. <p>

Research Scientists and Collaborators:<p>

	NREL PI:   Dennis Ojima<p>

	NREL Visiting Scientist:  Chuluun Togtohyn<p>

	External Collaborators:  <p>

		Other University:  Larry Tieszen (PI), Augustana College, SD<p>

		Government Agencies:  Tom Loveland, EROS Data Center, SD; Brad Reed, 					EROS, Data Center, SD<p>

		International:  Zhao Shidong, CISNRA, CAS, Beijing, PRC<p>

