<P>

<P> <A name="Personals"><H3>Personals</H3></A><P>
<P>
Jack and Betty Lou Hautaluoma will travel to San Diego, CA,
April 28, to attend the official presentation of "The
Outstanding Lawyer Award" to their daughter, Jodi, in
recognition of an excellent job done on her first court trial. 
<P>
<P>
Connor Stohlgren (age 11 3/4, 6th grade) was awarded "Best
of Fair" at the Timnath Elementary School 1994 Science Fair. 
His seven week project entitled "Will the Greenhouse Affect
Grass Species?" involved 3 types of grasses, two watering
regimes, and 24 jam jars (four replicates each).  His father,
Tom, who never won a prize for his research, just stayed out
of the young scientist's way.  Connor competes in the PR-1
District Science Fair next week.  <P>
<P>
<B>Thought for the Day</B><P>
<P>
Ecosystem management without ecosystem science is like a 6-
year-old Little League team without a coach.  Let's Play
Ball!!<P>
<P>
<em u>                                          </em><P>
